functions.doc: Executes the DSS capacity function. Start is the per unit load multiplier for the current year at which to start the search. Increment is the per unit value by which the load increments for each step of the analysis. The program sets the load at the Start value the PRESENT YEAR (including growth) and increments the load until something in thecircuit reports an overload or undervoltage violation. The function returns the total load at which the violation occurs or the peak load for the present year if no violations.
